OL,7,FWhen Joanne Findlay ended up homeless
OL,8,Fas a teenager and living in a B&B with
OL,9,Fpeople much older than her, it was a
OL,10,Ffrightening experience. End Youth
OL,11,FHomelessness member charity Aberdeen
OL,12,FFoyer came to her rescue ` and now she
OL,13,Fworks for them helping other young
OL,14,Fpeople out of homelessness.
OL,16,FJoanne Findlay's relationship with her
OL,17,Fparents broke down when she was 17 and
OL,18,Fshe says she was asked to leave the
OL,19,Ffamily home. She admits she initially
OL,20,Fthought it was exciting and a bit of an
OL,21,Fadventure.
OL,3,CChristmas appeal: 'It was terrifying
OL,4,Cbeing homeless at 17. I was saved, now
OL,5,CI help others'
